1
00:00:26,250 --> 00:00:30,590
Beer! Get your beer!

2
00:00:28,800 --> 00:00:32,010
Alright, it's that time of year!

3
00:00:32,010 --> 00:00:34,130
The annual magic festival...

4
00:00:34,130 --> 00:00:37,400
The Grand Magic Games!

5
00:02:12,560 --> 00:02:14,580
That's some cheering.

6
00:02:15,220 --> 00:02:17,640
I didn't realize there'd be so many people.

7
00:02:17,760 --> 00:02:20,350
Both Fiore wizards

8
00:02:20,350 --> 00:02:23,260
and a ton of regular spectators, it seems.

9
00:02:24,600 --> 00:02:26,950
Y'know, I really don't like this outfit.

10
00:02:26,950 --> 00:02:29,330
It's too late to whine about it now!

11
00:02:29,330 --> 00:02:32,790
Master told us to wear 
matching team colors, right?

12
00:02:34,590 --> 00:02:37,460
I like mine. It's cute.

13
00:02:37,480 --> 00:02:39,480
Yep. Me too.

14
00:02:39,480 --> 00:02:41,510
Say that after you put clothes on!

15
00:02:42,600 --> 00:02:44,300
I don't believe this,

16
00:02:44,650 --> 00:02:47,100
but I'm supposed to put this on...?

17
00:02:49,150 --> 00:02:50,750
That's great!

18
00:02:50,750 --> 00:02:53,520
You won't fit into Wendy's outfit, huh?

19
00:02:53,520 --> 00:02:56,450
The problem is your body's gotten too big.

20
00:02:58,710 --> 00:03:02,070
I was jazzed to participate in this,

21
00:03:02,540 --> 00:03:05,110
but is Wendy okay?

22
00:03:09,230 --> 00:03:10,360
Wendy!

23
00:03:14,050 --> 00:03:15,310
Where was she?!

24
00:03:15,310 --> 00:03:18,410
Near some bushes in the palace garden.

25
00:03:20,480 --> 00:03:21,550
Wendy!

26
00:03:26,420 --> 00:03:27,840
Natsu-san...

27
00:03:28,770 --> 00:03:30,100
What happened?

28
00:03:30,960 --> 00:03:32,630
I'm sorry...

29
00:03:32,850 --> 00:03:36,340
I can't... really remember...

30
00:03:37,490 --> 00:03:38,470
Wendy...

31
00:03:38,470 --> 00:03:40,970
It seems she has magic deficiency disease.

32
00:03:43,690 --> 00:03:44,870
Poluchka-san!

33
00:03:45,220 --> 00:03:46,830
What are you doing here?

34
00:03:47,050 --> 00:03:48,870
Something wrong with coming to cheer you on?

35
00:03:49,060 --> 00:03:50,210
No!

36
00:03:50,410 --> 00:03:52,610
You don't need to be that nervous around me.

37
00:03:53,100 --> 00:03:55,780
I'm not going to eat you up.

38
00:03:55,860 --> 00:03:57,070
Right...

39
00:03:57,070 --> 00:03:59,170
I heard what's going on with you

40
00:03:59,310 --> 00:04:01,670
and it made me worried, so here I am.

41
00:04:02,070 --> 00:04:03,110
Let me have a look.

42
00:04:04,700 --> 00:04:08,260
Just before, you said she has 
magic deficiency disease...

43
00:04:08,260 --> 00:04:09,210
Yes.

44
00:04:09,480 --> 00:04:11,840
Magic deficiency disease is when

45
00:04:11,850 --> 00:04:14,710
the sudden loss of a 
great deal of magic power

46
00:04:14,710 --> 00:04:17,850
causes all of the muscles to weaken.

47
00:04:18,840 --> 00:04:21,680
If she's allowed to rest for 
a while, she'll recover.

48
00:04:22,250 --> 00:04:23,740
What happened?

49
00:04:24,320 --> 00:04:26,640
I don't really remember it clearly,

50
00:04:26,860 --> 00:04:30,990
but there was some kind of black animal...

51
00:04:41,500 --> 00:04:42,610
Wendy...

52
00:04:42,810 --> 00:04:45,260
I'm sorry, everyone...

53
00:04:45,510 --> 00:04:48,620
After all the training I did, I...

54
00:04:48,890 --> 00:04:50,600
I can't participate...

55
00:04:55,220 --> 00:04:56,560
Elfman-san...

56
00:04:59,040 --> 00:05:02,570
Please compete in my place.

57
00:05:04,680 --> 00:05:07,320
Of course! Leave it to me!

58
00:05:07,850 --> 00:05:10,110
Okay, everyone leave.

59
00:05:10,640 --> 00:05:12,740
She needs her rest now!

60
00:05:13,100 --> 00:05:14,170
Let's go.

61
00:05:14,370 --> 00:05:18,540
The only thing we can do right now 
is compete in the Grand Magic Games.

62
00:05:18,540 --> 00:05:22,670
But that's not all of it, right? We have 
to become Fiore's number one guild!

63
00:05:30,780 --> 00:05:32,680
Oh, quit crying.

64
00:05:33,050 --> 00:05:36,950
The Grand Magic Games is a 
festival that lasts seven days.

65
00:05:37,500 --> 00:05:40,200
If you recover, you should 
be able to take part.

66
00:05:42,300 --> 00:05:45,590
On my honor as the advising 
apothecary of Fairy Tail,

67
00:05:45,870 --> 00:05:47,750
I swear I'll cure you!

68
00:05:49,850 --> 00:05:52,180
Thank you, Grandine.

69
00:05:52,360 --> 00:05:54,720
Don't call me by that name!

70
00:05:58,670 --> 00:06:00,510
New Guild!

71
00:06:04,670 --> 00:06:06,460
Is the villain who harmed Wendy

72
00:06:06,500 --> 00:06:09,140
someone connected to this tournament?

73
00:06:09,140 --> 00:06:11,430
It's possible.

74
00:06:11,440 --> 00:06:15,450
Someone trying to weaken us? Or...

75
00:06:15,450 --> 00:06:17,600
All we can do now is do this!

76
00:06:17,600 --> 00:06:20,730
We've gotta do our best, 
for Wendy's sake, too!

77
00:06:21,150 --> 00:06:24,740
Alright, in just a moment, the curtain 
will rise on the Grand Magic Games.

78
00:06:24,850 --> 00:06:27,540
I'm your emcee, Chapati Rola,

79
00:06:27,540 --> 00:06:32,590
and next to me is former Council member, 
Yajima-san, who will provide the commentary.

80
00:06:32,840 --> 00:06:35,090
Yajima-san, I look forward 
to working together.

81
00:06:35,090 --> 00:06:36,370
Likewise.

82
00:06:36,370 --> 00:06:40,150
And I'd like to introduce our guest 
for day one, the current Miss Fiore,

83
00:06:40,150 --> 00:06:43,860
Blue Pegasus's Jenny Rearlight!

84
00:06:44,420 --> 00:06:47,010
We're gonna win this year!

85
00:06:47,560 --> 00:06:49,600
Alright, let's go!

86
00:06:52,550 --> 00:06:55,970
Okay, the players are 
about to take the field!

87
00:06:57,050 --> 00:07:00,940
Starting with the eighth-ranked team! 
Can they recapture their past glory?!

88
00:07:01,180 --> 00:07:03,730
The group whose name clashes 
with their rowdiness!

89
00:07:03,730 --> 00:07:08,480
Fairy Tail!

90
00:07:10,090 --> 00:07:11,760
What?!

91
00:07:12,330 --> 00:07:13,880
Booing, are they?!

92
00:07:13,880 --> 00:07:15,160
What the heck is this?!

93
00:07:15,160 --> 00:07:18,660
Fairy Tail has come in last place every 
year, but they survived the elimination round,

94
00:07:18,660 --> 00:07:21,290
though even in that, they were eighth place.

95
00:07:21,560 --> 00:07:24,410
Will the Tenrou bunch that created a sensation with their homecoming

96
00:07:24,410 --> 00:07:26,590
now become Fiore's number one?!

97
00:07:27,700 --> 00:07:28,800
Don't let it get to you.

98
00:07:29,380 --> 00:07:32,520
I'm just glad they're back.

99
00:07:32,520 --> 00:07:35,040
Congratulations, Fairy Tail.

100
00:07:35,040 --> 00:07:38,140
Let's start cheerin' 'em on!

101
00:07:38,140 --> 00:07:43,810
Hooray! Hooray! Hooray, Fairy Tail!

102
00:07:40,550 --> 00:07:43,410
As long as we've got the support of 
our comrades. That's all that counts.

103
00:07:43,430 --> 00:07:43,810
Yeah.

104
00:07:43,810 --> 00:07:49,210
Hooray, hooray, Fairy Tail! 
Hooray, hooray, Fairy Tail!

105
00:07:46,550 --> 00:07:47,570
What the heck is that?!

106
00:07:47,570 --> 00:07:48,580
I don't believe it!

107
00:07:48,580 --> 00:07:49,760
How...?!

108
00:07:49,850 --> 00:07:54,230
Hooray, hooray, Fairy Tail!

109
00:07:54,230 --> 00:07:57,090
Master Mavis!

110
00:07:58,570 --> 00:08:00,660
I've come to show my support.

111
00:08:00,660 --> 00:08:03,890
You came...

112
00:08:03,890 --> 00:08:05,490
It's fine!

113
00:08:05,490 --> 00:08:09,810
Only those bearing the 
guild's insignia can see me.

114
00:08:09,810 --> 00:08:13,880
I, uh, don't know if that's the issue...

115
00:08:13,950 --> 00:08:18,390
After all, I've got nothing to do being 
cooped up on Tenroujima all the time.

116
00:08:20,160 --> 00:08:23,740
It's encouraging having the 
first master here to watch us!

117
00:08:23,850 --> 00:08:25,650
Even though she's a ghost...

118
00:08:25,650 --> 00:08:28,910
Alright! Let's move on with the 
team that finished seventh,

119
00:08:28,910 --> 00:08:33,770
the hounds of hell, Quatro Cerberus!

120
00:08:33,770 --> 00:08:36,490
Wild Four!

121
00:08:36,490 --> 00:08:40,350
This is the year that we 
win, all you bastards!

122
00:08:40,350 --> 00:08:43,330
In sixth place, the all-female guild,

123
00:08:43,330 --> 00:08:48,840
the dancing girls of the 
great deep, Mermaid Heel!

124
00:08:49,550 --> 00:08:52,120
I never heard of that guild!

125
00:08:52,350 --> 00:08:55,790
In fifth place are the bright 
blue wings in pitch dark,

126
00:08:55,790 --> 00:08:58,230
Blue Pegasus!

127
00:08:58,230 --> 00:09:00,540
Do your best, everyone!

128
00:09:00,600 --> 00:09:05,500
Continuing with fourth place! The goddess 
of love and war, the holy destroyer,

129
00:09:05,500 --> 00:09:08,920
Lamia Scale!

130
00:09:08,920 --> 00:09:13,350
Why did you come in fourth place?! 
Were you slacking off, you idiots?!

131
00:09:13,350 --> 00:09:15,150
Sorry, Obaba-sama.

132
00:09:15,150 --> 00:09:17,320
I screwed up...

133
00:09:17,840 --> 00:09:19,210
Who the hell is she?

134
00:09:19,210 --> 00:09:21,870
What happened to her usual 
"love"? Where's the love?

135
00:09:21,870 --> 00:09:23,850
Cheria, don't get flustered.

136
00:09:23,850 --> 00:09:25,370
Sorry, Lyon.

137
00:09:25,370 --> 00:09:27,820
Cheria is Sherry's cousin.

138
00:09:27,820 --> 00:09:29,160
Cousin?

139
00:09:30,130 --> 00:09:31,670
She's totally strong!

140
00:09:31,670 --> 00:09:33,010
No, I'm not.

141
00:09:33,010 --> 00:09:35,580
I still don't have nearly enough love.

142
00:09:35,580 --> 00:09:36,970
I'm complimenting you!

143
00:09:36,970 --> 00:09:39,210
Don't blow your stack over that.

144
00:09:39,340 --> 00:09:41,730
I guess the cousin's all about love too, huh?

145
00:09:41,730 --> 00:09:44,310
Gray. Don't forget that promise.

146
00:09:45,370 --> 00:09:48,730
If we win, Juvia joins our guild.

147
00:09:48,730 --> 00:09:51,500
I don't remember agreeing to that,

148
00:09:51,500 --> 00:09:53,820
but we ain't gonna lose to you people.

149
00:09:54,090 --> 00:09:57,480
In that case, I'll take Erza-san.

150
00:09:57,480 --> 00:09:59,240
You're not taking me anywhere!

151
00:09:59,860 --> 00:10:02,030
As always, you exude an exquisite parfum...

152
00:10:02,300 --> 00:10:04,110
I'll choose you.

153
00:10:04,260 --> 00:10:06,840
Although it's not because 
I especially like you...

154
00:10:06,840 --> 00:10:10,170
Have you been acting like this 
for the past seven years?

155
00:10:10,170 --> 00:10:13,160
Then I choose Wendy-chan...

156
00:10:14,070 --> 00:10:17,890
You've sure grown. In an unfortunate way...

157
00:10:17,890 --> 00:10:19,050
Stupid.

158
00:10:19,520 --> 00:10:22,080
Maybe I'll join Mermaid Heel!

159
00:10:22,080 --> 00:10:23,800
That's off-topic!

160
00:10:23,800 --> 00:10:26,790
Hey, I haven't seen that 
person before either...

161
00:10:27,880 --> 00:10:29,100
Wild! Wild!

162
00:10:29,100 --> 00:10:30,990
Are you sure that's a person?!

163
00:10:29,560 --> 00:10:33,360
Wild Four!

164
00:10:33,360 --> 00:10:35,730
Next up, finishing third 
in the elimination round...

165
00:10:35,730 --> 00:10:40,780
Oh, my! This comes as a surprise! The first 
appearance of a guild, and in third place!

166
00:10:40,780 --> 00:10:45,460
The midnight mobile force, Raven Tail!

167
00:10:47,260 --> 00:10:49,330
Raven Tail?!

168
00:10:50,690 --> 00:10:54,590
That's the guild of the master's son, Ivan...

169
00:10:54,590 --> 00:10:56,280
But that's...

170
00:11:04,930 --> 00:11:07,290
...a Dark Guild!

171
00:11:15,380 --> 00:11:19,370
You're lettin' a guild like that 
participate in the Grand Magic Games?!

172
00:11:19,370 --> 00:11:21,210
Master, calm down.

173
00:11:21,440 --> 00:11:23,140
You'll fall from there...

174
00:11:25,490 --> 00:11:27,830
Certainly, I sense malice coming off of them.

175
00:11:28,150 --> 00:11:29,990
They said that's a Dark Guild.

176
00:11:29,990 --> 00:11:32,710
I don't think I've heard of them before.

177
00:11:33,500 --> 00:11:35,700
According to the official record,

178
00:11:35,700 --> 00:11:39,480
Raven Tail has been around 
for more than seven years,

179
00:11:39,480 --> 00:11:43,760
but they've only recently been 
recognized as a legitimate guild.

180
00:11:44,760 --> 00:11:47,720
Recognized by the Guild Federation,

181
00:11:47,720 --> 00:11:50,220
and not as a Dark Guild, right?

182
00:11:50,220 --> 00:11:53,740
Damn you, Ivan... How dare you?!

183
00:11:53,740 --> 00:11:56,520
How did you manage that?!

184
00:11:58,390 --> 00:12:02,060
Keep it down, Father.

185
00:12:02,400 --> 00:12:04,910
Don't spoil this day.

186
00:12:06,860 --> 00:12:08,620
Fairy Tail...

187
00:12:10,510 --> 00:12:13,330
The girl was just by way of greeting.

188
00:12:18,420 --> 00:12:20,470
You guys did that to Wendy...

189
00:12:20,600 --> 00:12:22,420
I'll get you for that!

190
00:12:28,610 --> 00:12:31,140
Let's enjoy the festival.

191
00:12:36,430 --> 00:12:37,680
Ivan...

192
00:12:37,680 --> 00:12:41,710
Alright, there are still two more teams 
that made it through the elimination round!

193
00:12:41,710 --> 00:12:44,670
That's right. There are still two more...

194
00:12:44,670 --> 00:12:46,990
One must be Sabertooth, right?

195
00:12:46,990 --> 00:12:48,320
And the other...

196
00:12:48,590 --> 00:12:51,410
The main guilds are all already out here...

197
00:12:51,800 --> 00:12:55,000
Was there another strong guild 
that kept itself hidden?

198
00:12:55,000 --> 00:12:58,500
Does it have a connection to the magic 
power that Jellal was talking about?

199
00:12:58,500 --> 00:13:02,480
The second-place finisher... 
oh, this is a shocker!

200
00:13:02,480 --> 00:13:05,380
Will they become the soaring 
key with tattered wings?

201
00:13:05,630 --> 00:13:07,840
The unbelievable, improbable...

202
00:13:08,840 --> 00:13:12,130
...Fairy Tail B Team!

203
00:13:12,130 --> 00:13:12,890
Nee-chan!

204
00:13:12,890 --> 00:13:13,660
Gajeel?!

205
00:13:13,660 --> 00:13:14,400
Juvia?!

206
00:13:14,400 --> 00:13:16,770
Isn't it against the rules 
for Laxus to be on the team?!

207
00:13:18,290 --> 00:13:20,520
Another Fairy Tail team...

208
00:13:20,520 --> 00:13:25,000
And what's Mystogan doin' there?!

209
00:13:25,840 --> 00:13:28,860
Don't tell me, you're... Jellal?!

210
00:13:30,430 --> 00:13:32,520
Seriously?!

211
00:13:38,890 --> 00:13:40,150
Juvia...

212
00:13:40,830 --> 00:13:43,250
That's the one you love, Lyon?

213
00:13:43,510 --> 00:13:47,330
That's Fairy Tail for you. 
Two teams made the cut...

214
00:13:47,530 --> 00:13:51,050
Laxus... and Gajeel...

215
00:13:52,160 --> 00:13:54,240
What the hell is this?!

216
00:13:54,340 --> 00:13:57,200
Why does Fairy Tail get two teams?!

217
00:13:57,250 --> 00:13:58,940
That's too wild!

218
00:13:59,350 --> 00:14:02,740
Well, it looks like a lot 
of people are up in arms

219
00:14:02,740 --> 00:14:06,310
over a revision of the rules 
this time, Yajima-san.

220
00:14:06,910 --> 00:14:11,030
For this tournament, each guild 
can have one team, which is nice,

221
00:14:11,030 --> 00:14:13,450
but they can also have 
two teams participating.

222
00:14:13,450 --> 00:14:16,520
I didn't hear anything about that, Master!

223
00:14:19,150 --> 00:14:23,400
You see that?! That's Fairy Tail!

224
00:14:23,400 --> 00:14:27,070
The final round will be a battle 
between all of the teams,

225
00:14:27,070 --> 00:14:30,900
but will members of the same guild 
be able to fight each other?

226
00:14:31,820 --> 00:14:34,960
I don't think they'd have 
a problem with it...

227
00:14:35,070 --> 00:14:37,360
But it's not really fair, is it?

228
00:14:37,390 --> 00:14:42,140
For example, if one member from 
each team competes in an event,

229
00:14:42,140 --> 00:14:45,150
it's like only Fairy Tail gets 
to fight as a pair, right?

230
00:14:45,150 --> 00:14:46,760
You're saying that out of over 100 teams,

231
00:14:46,760 --> 00:14:51,920
the two winning Fairy Tail 
teams have an advantage, yes?

232
00:14:53,130 --> 00:14:56,120
That is an advantage to them-mabo.

233
00:14:56,120 --> 00:14:57,410
Mabo?

234
00:14:59,120 --> 00:15:02,890
I see! That's how there were 
so many teams participating.

235
00:15:03,650 --> 00:15:05,990
Gimme a break!

236
00:15:09,050 --> 00:15:14,230
We may be in the same guild, but I go 
all out in a showdown an' show no mercy!

237
00:15:14,410 --> 00:15:17,070
You guys are competing as another 
team, so you're the enemy!

238
00:15:17,070 --> 00:15:18,990
I ain't gonna lose against you bastards!

239
00:15:18,990 --> 00:15:21,160
You took the words right out of my mouth...

240
00:15:21,210 --> 00:15:24,120
...eighth place team member.

241
00:15:25,310 --> 00:15:28,070
Gajeel's gotten a lot stronger.

242
00:15:28,070 --> 00:15:30,200
Not strong enough to beat Natsu!

243
00:15:30,200 --> 00:15:33,860
At any rate, B team looks totally tough!

244
00:15:34,450 --> 00:15:36,560
Let's all do our best, right, Elfman?

245
00:15:36,560 --> 00:15:37,990
Nee-chan...

246
00:15:38,350 --> 00:15:41,830
Jella... Mystogan... You...

247
00:15:42,220 --> 00:15:44,790
You've got a very understanding master.

248
00:15:45,100 --> 00:15:48,340
When I explained the circumstances 
to him, he consented readily.

249
00:15:48,780 --> 00:15:51,470
You said you wouldn't come near the venue.

250
00:15:51,470 --> 00:15:54,660
At the time, I hadn't yet 
thought of this method.

251
00:15:54,660 --> 00:15:58,060
It's an infraction of the rules. 
You're not a member of our guild.

252
00:15:58,060 --> 00:16:02,600
Though I've heard that Mystogan and 
I are the same person in a sense...

253
00:16:04,090 --> 00:16:06,300
Oh, don't get so huffy about it.

254
00:16:06,410 --> 00:16:10,020
This is a festival, right, Mystogan?

255
00:16:11,610 --> 00:16:13,740
That's right, Erza.

256
00:16:13,740 --> 00:16:15,860
But one thing, Mystogan...

257
00:16:16,200 --> 00:16:18,860
Mystogan is just a little more tight-lipped.

258
00:16:19,400 --> 00:16:20,540
Be careful.

259
00:16:20,840 --> 00:16:22,250
Understood.

260
00:16:22,940 --> 00:16:26,960
That masked person isn't a 
member of the guild, is he?

261
00:16:28,460 --> 00:16:31,500
I'm sorry! I'm sorry! I'm sorry!

262
00:16:31,500 --> 00:16:33,730
I told you not to do it.

263
00:16:33,730 --> 00:16:35,630
I tried to stop him.

264
00:16:37,040 --> 00:16:39,510
But he's not evil.

265
00:16:39,890 --> 00:16:44,760
Strangely enough, I sense that he has the same 
heart as those who bear the insignia of our guild.

266
00:16:45,020 --> 00:16:49,980
It's a long story, but in a sense, you 
could say he is a member of our guild.

267
00:16:49,980 --> 00:16:53,410
I see. So that's this world's Jellal.

268
00:16:53,410 --> 00:16:55,030
The prince...

269
00:16:55,630 --> 00:16:56,940
Is he strong?

270
00:16:56,940 --> 00:17:01,800
Oh, sure. He was formerly counted as 
one of the 10 Great Wizard Saints.

271
00:17:05,760 --> 00:17:07,120
I approve.

272
00:17:07,800 --> 00:17:10,540
So that Fairy Tail wins!

273
00:17:10,540 --> 00:17:12,300
That's the first master for you...

274
00:17:12,300 --> 00:17:15,300
Even if the logic is twisted, 
she doesn't care...

275
00:17:15,300 --> 00:17:17,930
That's our guild in a nutshell.

276
00:17:18,280 --> 00:17:21,360
So, have you noticed anything?

277
00:17:21,470 --> 00:17:24,990
Other than Raven Tail being 
suspicious, nothing especially.

278
00:17:24,990 --> 00:17:27,460
That guild is making its debut here, right?

279
00:17:27,460 --> 00:17:30,320
They don't mesh with the magic 
power I sense every year.

280
00:17:30,320 --> 00:17:33,930
How about you? Do you sense that 
magic power or whatever now?

281
00:17:33,930 --> 00:17:35,920
No. Not yet.

282
00:17:38,640 --> 00:17:40,550
Gajeel-chan...

283
00:17:40,850 --> 00:17:45,750
Alright, we've just got one 
more team left to introduce!

284
00:17:46,240 --> 00:17:48,830
That's right, you know who it is!

285
00:17:48,830 --> 00:17:53,500
They're the strongest, invincible, 
indisputable champions!

286
00:17:53,840 --> 00:17:57,420
Sabertooth!

287
00:18:12,670 --> 00:18:14,190
So here you are, huh?

288
00:18:14,190 --> 00:18:16,950
Let's have a good time, Natsu-san!

289
00:18:16,950 --> 00:18:19,490
Who the hell are you starin' at?!

290
00:18:19,570 --> 00:18:21,030
Gajeel...

291
00:18:25,040 --> 00:18:27,950
So that's Fiore's strongest guild?

292
00:18:27,950 --> 00:18:30,900
Good luck, Sting-kun!

293
00:18:30,900 --> 00:18:33,340
Fro is cheering you on, too!

294
00:18:33,340 --> 00:18:36,000
Are those Exceeds in the stands?!

295
00:18:36,000 --> 00:18:38,340
Don't you lose, Natsu!

296
00:18:38,340 --> 00:18:40,160
Gajeel, do your best!

297
00:18:40,160 --> 00:18:43,070
And now, all of the teams are here,

298
00:18:43,070 --> 00:18:46,200
but what are your impressions, Yajima-san?

299
00:18:47,290 --> 00:18:49,980
I envy their youth!

300
00:18:49,980 --> 00:18:52,350
That's not really what I meant...

301
00:18:54,350 --> 00:18:56,370
Okay, everyone, you've waited long enough.

302
00:18:56,370 --> 00:18:59,280
I'm going to announce the program of the Grand Magic Games!

303
00:19:07,660 --> 00:19:10,740
So there's a competition 
and battle every day?

304
00:19:10,740 --> 00:19:12,020
Battle, huh?

305
00:19:12,020 --> 00:19:13,710
Starting with the competition,

306
00:19:13,710 --> 00:19:16,890
points have already been 
divided among the teams,

307
00:19:16,890 --> 00:19:20,760
according to their ranking in the 
elimination round, from first to eighth.

308
00:19:21,030 --> 00:19:26,080
Now for the competition part, each team can 
select one of their members to take part.

309
00:19:26,080 --> 00:19:28,090
And for the battle part,

310
00:19:28,090 --> 00:19:30,880
the results of fan votes will 
be taken into consideration

311
00:19:30,880 --> 00:19:34,010
when the sponsors make the pairings.

312
00:19:34,010 --> 00:19:35,260
What?!

313
00:19:35,420 --> 00:19:38,010
They can decide on the 
match-ups however they want?!

314
00:19:38,180 --> 00:19:39,130
In other words...

315
00:19:39,130 --> 00:19:42,720
...if you're unlucky, you could exhaust your magic during the competition part,

316
00:19:42,720 --> 00:19:44,320
then be forced into battle.

317
00:19:44,320 --> 00:19:46,670
The rules for the battle part are simple.

318
00:19:46,670 --> 00:19:49,310
As you can see, the teams 
face off against each other,

319
00:19:49,310 --> 00:19:51,240
with the winning team receiving ten points

320
00:19:51,240 --> 00:19:53,260
and the losing team getting zero points.

321
00:19:53,260 --> 00:19:56,460
In the case of a tie, both 
teams will receive five points.

322
00:19:56,780 --> 00:20:00,210
And now, the Grand Magic Games' opening game!

323
00:20:00,210 --> 00:20:02,340
Let's begin "Hidden"!

324
00:20:04,260 --> 00:20:05,800
Hidden...?

325
00:20:05,800 --> 00:20:07,640
What kind of a game is that?!

326
00:20:07,640 --> 00:20:09,920
One person from each team will compete.

327
00:20:09,920 --> 00:20:14,140
I'll explain the rules of the game after 
all of the players are on the field.

328
00:20:14,140 --> 00:20:15,820
Leave this one to me!

329
00:20:15,820 --> 00:20:18,370
Never forget! Your soul is always...

330
00:20:18,370 --> 00:20:21,050
Wild Four!

331
00:20:21,730 --> 00:20:26,610
The first person to step up 
is Quatro Cerberus's Yeager!

332
00:20:26,610 --> 00:20:29,680
Let me check out the first one!

333
00:20:29,680 --> 00:20:30,700
You have permission.

334
00:20:31,760 --> 00:20:35,820
From Mermaid Heel, Beth Vanderwood!

335
00:20:35,950 --> 00:20:38,460
Nalpudding, you go.

336
00:20:38,460 --> 00:20:40,380
Sure thing.

337
00:20:41,370 --> 00:20:45,250
From Raven Tail, Nalpudding!

338
00:20:45,250 --> 00:20:46,430
I'll do this one.

339
00:20:46,430 --> 00:20:48,240
Eve-kun is our first person.

340
00:20:48,240 --> 00:20:50,350
Eve-kun is our first person!

341
00:20:51,850 --> 00:20:56,650
Eve has been called out! 
From Blue Pegasus, Eve Tilm!

342
00:20:56,650 --> 00:21:01,320
I'll do it. The singing of 
the birds is pleasant today.

343
00:21:02,350 --> 00:21:06,630
All eyes are on Sabertooth, and they go with 
the minstrel who sings to the red moon!

344
00:21:06,630 --> 00:21:09,030
Rufus is here!

345
00:21:10,380 --> 00:21:13,410
Why are they makin' such a fuss?! Idiots!

346
00:21:13,550 --> 00:21:15,410
I don't know what the rules of the game are,

347
00:21:15,410 --> 00:21:19,490
but the name is "Hidden", so 
maybe hiding is necessary.

348
00:21:19,520 --> 00:21:23,130
If only Wendy were here... She's little...

349
00:21:24,650 --> 00:21:28,530
I'll go first! I'll do it as a Man!

350
00:21:28,530 --> 00:21:32,010
Exactly what part of you 
is "hidden", meatball?!

351
00:21:32,050 --> 00:21:36,100
Being small may be the advantage here, 
so it should be either me or Yuuka.

352
00:21:36,100 --> 00:21:37,650
Don't call me small!

353
00:21:37,650 --> 00:21:38,870
No.

354
00:21:38,870 --> 00:21:40,910
I'm going to take off like 
a rocket from the start.

355
00:21:40,970 --> 00:21:42,400
I'll do it.

356
00:21:43,180 --> 00:21:46,990
From Lamia Scale, Lyon Vastia!

357
00:21:46,990 --> 00:21:50,300
Huh. In that case, I'll be in it, too.

358
00:21:50,450 --> 00:21:53,460
You can show me what this tournament is like.

359
00:21:54,250 --> 00:21:58,660
From Fairy Tail A Team, Gray Fullbuster!

360
00:22:00,140 --> 00:22:02,700
If Gray-sama is going to 
be in it, then so is Juvia!

361
00:22:02,700 --> 00:22:05,960
Hey! If you lose on purpose, 
there'll be hell to pay!

362
00:22:07,060 --> 00:22:10,930
From Fairy Tail B Team, Juvia Lockser!

363
00:22:11,330 --> 00:22:14,350
All of the participating players 
from the eight teams are set!

364
00:22:14,350 --> 00:22:19,360
And now for the rules of 
the opening game, "Hidden"!

365
00:23:56,140 --> 00:23:57,900
Look at all the Grays!

366
00:23:57,950 --> 00:24:00,040
Juvia is thrilled, huh?

367
00:24:00,040 --> 00:24:02,250
She's happy with a copy? Weirdo!

368
00:24:02,250 --> 00:24:04,960
I wish I could use Copy Magic, too...

369
00:24:04,960 --> 00:24:06,040
What would you do with it?

370
00:24:06,040 --> 00:24:09,250
Make tons of copies of my favorite fish!

371
00:24:09,250 --> 00:24:11,020
Can you eat copies of fish?

372
00:24:11,020 --> 00:24:13,730
Come on! Don't throw cold water on my dreams!

373
00:24:13,800 --> 00:24:16,390
Next time: On a Night of Falling Stars!

374
00:24:16,960 --> 00:24:20,390
I'll make a lot of angry Erzas 
to come after you, Natsu!

375
00:24:20,880 --> 00:24:23,550
No! Anything but that!

